$ Excel: View -> Window -> Freeze Pane

*→ Microsoft/Office/Excel/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/View/Window[View -> Window] -> Freeze Pane* allows to keep a specified portion (such as first row or left most column) of a → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Worksheet visible while navigating through the rest of the worksheet.

In → development/languages/VBA, this functionality is exposed through → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Window#excel-window-freezePanes[`window.freezePanes`].

sa:

  A → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Window[window's] → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Window/split[`.split`] properties.

  Libre Office Calc's → development/Software/LibreOffice/Calc/GUI/menu/View/Freeze/Cells[View -> Freeze Pane]
